  "privacyTitle": "Privacy Policy",
  "privacyLastUpdated": "Last updated: March 1, 2026",
  "privacyS1Title": "1. Information We Collect",
  "privacyS1Body": "At Atrio we collect different types of information to provide and improve our services:\n\n• Registration information: name, email, phone number and profile photo.\n\n• Verification information: identity documents for host verification (KYC).\n\n• Usage data: app interactions, searches, bookings, messages sent, and preferences.\n\n• Device information: model, operating system, unique identifiers, and network data.\n\n• Location data: with your consent, to show relevant results near you.",
  "privacyS2Title": "2. Use of Information",
  "privacyS2Body": "We use your personal information to:\n\n• Facilitate account creation and management\n• Process bookings and payment transactions\n• Efficiently connect users with hosts\n• Send relevant notifications about bookings and messages\n• Improve and personalize your platform experience\n• Prevent fraud and ensure community safety\n• Comply with legal and regulatory obligations\n• Generate anonymous statistical analysis to improve the service",
  "privacyS3Title": "3. Information Sharing",
  "privacyS3Body": "Atrio does not sell your personal information to third parties. We may share limited information in the following cases:\n\n• With other users: when you make or receive a booking, we share the information necessary to complete the transaction (name, photo, contact details).\n\n• Service providers: payment processors, cloud storage services, and analytics tools that help us operate the platform.\n\n• Legal requirements: when necessary to comply with law, legal processes, or government requests.",
  "privacyS4Title": "4. Storage and Security",
  "privacyS4Body": "Your information is stored on secure servers with end-to-end encryption. We implement technical and organizational security measures to protect your data against unauthorized access, alteration, disclosure, or destruction. Payment data is processed through PCI DSS certified providers and is never stored on our servers.",
  "privacyS5Title": "5. Data Retention",
  "privacyS5Body": "We retain your personal information while your account is active or as necessary to provide you with services. If you request account deletion, we will delete or anonymize your personal information within 30 days, except when required by law to retain certain data for a specific period.",
  "privacyS6Title": "6. Your Rights",
  "privacyS6Body": "You have the right to:\n\n• Access your personal data stored on our platform\n• Rectify inaccurate or outdated information\n• Request deletion of your personal data\n• Object to processing of your data for specific purposes\n• Request portability of your data in a structured format\n• Withdraw your consent at any time\n\nTo exercise these rights, contact us at privacy@atriocompany.cloud",
  "privacyS7Title": "7. Cookies and Similar Technologies",
  "privacyS7Body": "We use cookies and similar technologies to improve your experience, remember your preferences, and analyze platform usage. You can configure your device to reject cookies, although this may affect certain app features.",
  "privacyS8Title": "8. Minors",
  "privacyS8Body": "Atrio is not directed at individuals under 18 years old. We do not knowingly collect personal information from minors. If we discover we have collected information from a minor, we will take steps to remove that information from our records.",
  "privacyS9Title": "9. Changes to This Policy",
  "privacyS9Body": "We may update this privacy policy periodically to reflect changes in our information practices. We will notify you of significant changes through the app or by email. We recommend reviewing this policy regularly.",
  "privacyS10Title": "10. Contact",
  "privacyS10Body": "If you have questions about this privacy policy or how we handle your personal information, you can contact us:\n\n• Email: privacy@atriocompany.cloud\n• In-app Help Center\n• Data Protection Officer: dpo@atriocompany.cloud",
  "termsTitle": "Terms and Conditions",
  "termsHeader": "Terms and Conditions of Use",
  "termsLastUpdated": "Last updated: March 1, 2026",
  "termsS1Title": "1. Acceptance of Terms",
  "termsS1Body": "By accessing and using the Atrio application (\"the Platform\"), you agree to be bound by these Terms and Conditions of Use. If you disagree with any part of these terms, you may not access or use our services. These terms constitute a legally binding agreement between you and Atrio Technologies SpA",
  "termsS2Title": "2. Service Description",
  "termsS2Body": "Atrio is a premium marketplace platform that connects hosts with users, facilitating the booking of spaces, experiences, and professional services. The Platform acts as an intermediary between the parties, providing the technological tools necessary for users to publish, discover, and book offers.",
  "termsS3Title": "3. Registration and User Accounts",
  "termsS3Body": "To use certain Atrio services, you must create an account by providing accurate and complete information. You are responsible for maintaining the confidentiality of your login credentials and for all activities that occur under your account. You must notify us immediately of any unauthorized use of your account or any security breach.",
  "termsS4Title": "4. User Roles",
  "termsS4Body": "Users can operate in two modes within Atrio:\n\n• User Mode: Allows exploring, searching, and booking spaces, experiences, and services published by hosts.\n\n• Host Mode: Allows publishing and managing spaces, experiences, and services, receiving bookings, and managing income through the control panel.",
  "termsS5Title": "5. Bookings and Payments",
  "termsS5Body": "All transactions are processed through our authorized payment providers. Atrio charges a service fee on each completed transaction. Fees, commissions, and additional charges will be transparently displayed before confirming any booking. Hosts will receive their payments according to the established disbursement schedule.",
  "termsS6Title": "6. Cancellations and Refunds",
  "termsS6Body": "Cancellation policies vary by booking type and the conditions set by each host. Users may cancel bookings according to the applicable policy. Refunds will be processed within 5-10 business days following cancellation approval, using the same original payment method.",
  "termsS7Title": "7. User Conduct",
  "termsS7Body": "Users agree to:\n\n• Not use the platform for illegal or unauthorized purposes\n• Not publish false, misleading, or fraudulent content\n• Respect third-party intellectual property rights\n• Maintain respectful conduct in all interactions\n• Not attempt to circumvent platform security measures\n• Not manipulate reviews or ratings",
  "termsS8Title": "8. Intellectual Property",
  "termsS8Body": "All Atrio content, including but not limited to texts, graphics, logos, icons, images, audio clips, digital downloads, and data compilations, is the property of Atrio Technologies SpA or its content providers and is protected by applicable intellectual property laws.",
  "termsS9Title": "9. Limitation of Liability",
  "termsS9Body": "Atrio acts as an intermediary and is not responsible for the actions, conduct, or content of users. We do not guarantee the quality, safety, or legality of the spaces, experiences, or services published. Users assume full responsibility for their interactions and transactions carried out through the platform.",
  "termsS10Title": "10. Modifications",
  "termsS10Body": "Atrio reserves the right to modify these terms at any time. Modifications will take effect upon publication on the platform. Continued use of the application after any modification constitutes your acceptance of the new terms.",
  "termsS11Title": "11. Contact",
  "termsS11Body": "For inquiries about these terms, you may contact us through:\n\n• Email: legal@atriocompany.cloud\n• In-app Help Center\n• Address: Atrio Technologies SpA, Santiago de Chile, Chile",

